      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# **Notion Google Play Review Preprocessing & Stopwords**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mkvVNzklM7fi"
      }
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## **⚙️ Process Description**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mkvVNzklM7fi"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "The preprocessing stage is conducted to transform raw user reviews from the Notion application into clean, structured, and analyzable text data. Raw text often contains inconsistencies, noise, and irrelevant elements that may reduce the accuracy of further analysis such as sentiment classification or text mining.\n",
        "\n",
        "The preprocessing pipeline consists of several sequential steps:\n",
        "\n",
        "| Step | Task | Description | Tool / Method |\n",
        "|------|------|------------|---------------|\n",
        "| 1 | Data Cleaning | Removed missing, empty, and inconsistent data to ensure dataset quality and reliability. | pandas |\n",
        "| 2 | Remove Duplicates | Eliminated duplicate review entries to avoid bias in analysis. | pandas |\n",
        "| 3 | Case Folding | Converted all text into lowercase to standardize word representation. | str.lower() |\n",
        "| 4 | Slang Normalization  | Replaced informal or abbreviated words with their standard forms to improve text clarity. | custom dictionary |\n",
        "| 5 | Noise Removal | Removed URLs, numbers, punctuation, symbols, and excessive whitespace to reduce noise. | re, string |\n",
        "| 6 | Tokenization | Split sentences into individual words (tokens) for detailed text processing. | NLTK word_tokenize |\n",
        "| 7 | Stopword Removal | Filtered out common English words with low semantic value. | NLTK stopwords |\n",
        "| 8 | Stemming | Reduced words to their root form to maintain consistency in analysis. | NLTK PorterStemmer |\n",
        "| 9 | Frequent Words Analysis  | Identified the most common words to understand dominant terms in the dataset. | Counter |\n",
        "| 10 | Rare Words Removal | Removed infrequent words that may introduce noise in the analysis. | frequency threshold |\n",
        "| 11 | Text Reconstruction | Rejoined processed tokens into clean text for further analysis. | join() |\n",
        "| 12 | Data Export | Saved the cleaned dataset for subsequent analysis or modeling. | pandas |"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "sQJ3U9PTNBOX"
      }
    },
